cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI 

This paper discusses fairness in algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses graphical models, which are commonly used in causal inference and decision-making, making cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) possible sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper touches on the social implications of algorithmic fairness, which could place it in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
